<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: Component_mounting_feature
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_feature">
<note> The local rules for this entity have not been fully updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

A <b>component_mounting_feature</b> is a  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/>.  A <b>component_mounting_feature</b>
implements the ARM concept of <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_design:arm:Assembly_module_design_arm.Component_mounting_feature"/>
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_mounting_feature.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_feature.wr:wr1">
The <b>component_mounting_feature</b> shall be an aspect of the shape of a  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:mim:Physical_unit_design_view_mim.component_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_mounting_feature.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_feature.wr:wr2">
The <b>component_mounting_feature</b> shall not be any of the following:  <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:mim:Layered_interconnect_module_design_mim.inter_stratum_feature"/>,
 <express_ref linkend="Layered_interconnect_module_design:mim:Layered_interconnect_module_design_mim.probe_access_area"/>, land.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_mounting_feature.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_feature.wr:wr3">
The <b>component_mounting_feature</b> shall have at most one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation"/>
with a name of 'planar projected shape'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_mounting_feature.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_feature.wr:wr4">
The <b>component_mounting_feature</b> shall have at most one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation"/>
with a name of '3d bound volume shape'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_mounting_feature.WR5
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_feature.wr:wr5">
If the <b>component_mounting_feature</b> has a description of 'component feature',
it shall relate to at most one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> to specify the
'design usage'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_mounting_feature.WR6
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_feature.wr:wr6">
The <b>component_mounting_feature</b> shall be related to at most one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> as an 'instantiated feature'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: Packaged_component
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.packaged_component">
<note> The local rules for this entity have not been fully updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

A <b>packaged_component</b> is a  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:mim:Physical_unit_design_view_mim.component_definition"/> that implements the ARM concepts
of:
</p><ul> 
<li> <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_design:arm:Assembly_module_design_arm.Packaged_component"/></li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_with_packaged_connector_component:arm:Assembly_module_with_packaged_connector_component_arm.Packaged_connector_component"/></li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Unknown:arm:Unknown_arm.Routed_packaged_component"/></li>
</ul>
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Packaged_component.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.packaged_component.wr:wr1">
The <b>packaged_component</b> shall be related, as the 'instantiated part',
to exactly one  <express_ref linkend="Packaged_part_black_box_model:mim:Packaged_part_black_box_model_mim.packaged_part"/>, externally_defined_packaged_part, or
library_defined_packaged_part that is in the 'physical design usage'
 <express_ref linkend="application_context_schema:ir_express:application_context_schema.product_definition_context"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Packaged_component.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.packaged_component.wr:wr2">
The <b>packaged_component</b> shall be related, as the 'package alternate',
to at most one package, externally_defined_package, or
library_defined_package that has a description of 'altered package'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Packaged_component.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.packaged_component.wr:wr3">
The <b>packaged_component</b> shall have at least one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> that is a
 <express_ref linkend="Component_feature:mim:Component_feature_mim.component_terminal"/> with a description of 'packaged component join terminal'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Packaged_component.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.packaged_component.wr:wr4">
If the <b>packaged_component</b> has description of 'packaged connector
component', the <b>packaged_component</b> shall be related, as the 'instantiated
part', to exactly one  <express_ref linkend="Packaged_part_black_box_model:mim:Packaged_part_black_box_model_mim.packaged_part"/>, externally_defined_packaged_part, or
library_defined_packaged_part that is in the 'packaged connector'
 <express_ref linkend="application_context_schema:ir_express:application_context_schema.product_definition_context"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Packaged_component.WR5
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.packaged_component.wr:wr5">
If the <b>packaged_component</b> has a description of 'packaged connector
component', it shall have at least one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> that is a 
 <express_ref linkend="Interface_component:mim:Interface_component_mim.component_interface_terminal"/> with a description of 
'packaged component join terminal'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Packaged_component.WR6
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.packaged_component.wr:wr6">
If the <b>packaged_component</b> has a description of 'routed packaged
component', it shall have exactly one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> that has exactly one
 <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.property_definition"/> that is associated to exactly one representation.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: Routed_physical_component
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.routed_physical_component">
<note> The local rules for this entity have not been fully updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

A <b>routed_physical_component</b> is a  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:mim:Physical_unit_design_view_mim.component_definition"/> that implements the ARM concept
of <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_design:arm:Assembly_module_design_arm.Routed_physical_component"/>
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Routed_physical_component.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.routed_physical_component.wr:wr1">
The <b>routed_physical_component</b> shall be related, as the 'instantiated part',
to exactly one  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_usage_view:mim:Physical_unit_usage_view_mim.physical_unit"/> that is in the 'physical design usage'
 <express_ref linkend="application_context_schema:ir_express:application_context_schema.product_definition_context"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Routed_physical_component.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.routed_physical_component.wr:wr2">
The <b>routed_physical_component</b> shall not have a description of 'laminate component'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: Component_feature_external_reference_unique_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_feature_external_reference_unique_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>component_feature_external_reference_unique_constraint</b> rule constrains the
 <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.property_definition_representation"/> population members, that fill the role of ARM
component_feature_external_reference, so that the combination of ARM name
and ARM associated_component attributes shall be unique within the population.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_feature_external_reference_unique_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_feature_external_reference_unique_constraint.wr:wr1">
Every instance of  <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> with a name of
'component feature external reference' must have a unique combination of
description attributes and representation entities where the representations
have the descriptive_representation_items in their items attribute and the
representations have a name of 'component external reference'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: Component_external_reference_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_external_reference_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>component_external_reference_constraint</b> rule constrains the use of a representation when it is used as a component external reference.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_external_reference_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_external_reference_constraint.wr:wr1">
Each representation with a name of 'component external reference'
shall contain a  <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> with a name of 'design owner'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_external_reference_constraint.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_external_reference_constraint.wr:wr2">
Each representation with a name of 'component external reference'
shall contain a  <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> with a name of 'part number'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_external_reference_constraint.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_external_reference_constraint.wr:wr3">
Each representation with a name of 'component external reference'
shall contain a  <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> with a name of 'revision code'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_external_reference_constraint.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_external_reference_constraint.wr:wr4">
Each representation with a name of 'component external reference'
shall contain a  <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> with a name of 'product definition id'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_external_reference_constraint.WR5
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_external_reference_constraint.wr:wr5">
Each representation with a name of 'component external reference'
shall contain a  <express_ref linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> with a name of 'reference designation'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: Component_mounting_clearance_relationship_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_clearance_relationship_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>component_mounting_clearance_relationship_constraint</b> rule
constrain the items of a representation and constrain the usage of that 
representation when it is used as a component mounting clearance.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_mounting_clearance_relationship_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_mounting_clearance_relationship_constraint.wr:wr1">
IF the representation name = 'mounting clearance' it shall contain one item that 
is a  <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.length_measure_with_unit"/> that has a name = 'minimum height'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Rule: Component_overlap_relationship_constraint
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_overlap_relationship_constraint">
<note> This rule may not have been updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

The <b>component_overlap_relationship_constraint</b> rule
constrain the items of a representation and constrain the usage of that 
representation when it is used as a component overlap clearance.
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Component_overlap_relationship_constraint.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_design_mim.component_overlap_relationship_constraint.wr:wr1">
IF the representation name = 'overlap clearance' it shall contain one item that 
is a  <express_ref linkend="measure_schema:ir_express:measure_schema.length_measure_with_unit"/> that has a name = 'minimum clearance'.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
